dialogue: Ross?
Hey it’s Mona! From the wedding.
Hi!
I’m good except umm, you still owe me a dance.
I think I might need one more cup of coffee.
Okay.
You think so? I’ve always kinda hated it.
Uh-huh.
Really?! Well see? I never knew about her.
Oh good. Now there’ll be someone there who likes my name.
Hi!
Sure.
Yeah.
Ohhhh!
How cute was that?
So, is it my turn now?
Uh, that’s okay. You can dance with her first.
That is so sweet!
No, I mean it. There are so few genuinely nice guys out there.
It’s Joey right?
Hi!
Umm, actually I’m just a nurse.
Hi!
Wait-wait! You’re umm, you’re a potato…
And the antennae…Oh my God you’re Spudnik!
Hey, you guys could arm wrestle.
So it was really cool seeing you lecture today.
Oh no-no, I-I had my eyes closed so I could concentrate and y’know take it all in.
So, I gotta get going.
Yeah.
Oh wow! So, you’re more than just dinosaurs.
Oh my God! Oh my God! I’m so sorry!
You got Rachel pregnant?!
What?!
Wh…
Tramp?!
How could you have kept all of this from me?
Oh good, you’re here. Yeah, and I was worried that it was going to be uncomfortable.
How can I be sure on that?
Y’know, I-I-I just…I don’t want to get in the middle of something so complicated.
I’m not sure yet. Why didn’t you just tell me about all this?
Yeah? Well you still shoulda told me.
No-no that’s a man’s shirt.
Ross, what are you doing?!

Yeah, you still have feelings for me. And-and to be honest, I-I still have feelings for you. And I wish that we can work it out Ross, but we can’t. It’s too complicated with you and Rachel and the baby, I-I just… It just wasn’t meant to be.
Hi!
Good.
I brought you back a present.
I think it’s interesting.
I missed you, too! So, how was your week?
How exciting!
Oh no.
So, what’d you tell him?
Change of plans, I made you a special Valentine’s dinner! Surprise!
Seriously, what is she doing?
Why?
Okay, but it’s Valentine’s Day!
Can’t we just ask her to go?
Oh, my God! She has food delivered here?
You got another ex-wife back there?
Oh, Rachel! Wait! Hey, I hope you don’t take this the wrong way, but, but, um… what are you doing?
No, no. Listen, Ross is too nice to say anything, but this is his apartment, and, and, we gotta have some boundaries, so why don’t you go back to your place and give us some privacy?
Hi! Look! I got our pictures developed from Rockefeller Center.
Okay. Okay, here’s a good one of us.
Y’know, every year I say I’m gonna send out holiday cards and I never do it. Do you wanna, do you wanna send this one out together?
Yeah, y’know. Happy holidays from Mona and Ross. It’ll be cute, okay?
Oh, I gotta get to work. So call me later?
Bye guys.
Hi!
Hey, I went by the photo shop, take a look, here is a mockup of our card. What do you think?
Now, do you think it should say, "Love Ross and Mona?"
How many did you want? I’m getting a hundred.
Really? Why not?
Oh y’know, I didn’t think of it that way. You’re right. You’re right. So, can I ask you a question?
Where are we?
Y’know, like where are we? Where is this relationship going?
I mean I love spending time with you, y’know I just—I hope we’re moving forward. I mean, we should probably talk about that. Don’t you think?
What?
Okay. I—But I think we should still have this conversation.
Yeah, I-I think I suggested that.
Okay.
I’m sorry, so umm, so where are we?
Okay…
Really?!
You don’t think this is too fast.
I don’t understand. You-you give me a key to your apartment and then you change the lock.
Umm, I-I thought we were moving forward and now you’re-you’re sending me all these mixed signals. What are you trying to tell me?
What?
